{"lemma":"ثَوْبِ","slug":"ثَوْبِ","root":"ث.#.ب","root_slug":"ث-_-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-_-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ثَوْبِ","root":"ثوب","pos":"V","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4796","n4802"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dress, garment"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cloth, material"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"outward appearance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clothes, clothing","tags":["in-plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/θawb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4796","headword_ar":"ثوِّب","root":"vwb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tavowiybN","text_ar":"تَثْوِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1, first sentence. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vwab baEoda xaSaASapK","text_ar":"ثوَب بَعْدَ خَصَاصَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He returned to a state of richness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"competence, after poverty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"straitness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being in an evil condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tavowiybN","text_ar":"تَثْوِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summoning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to prayer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to other things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) is said to be from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ a garment, ” (Mgh,) because a man, when he comes crying out for aid, makes a sign with his garment, (M, Mgh,) moving it about, raising his hand with it, in order that he to whom he calls may see it, (Mgh,) and this action is like a calling, or summoning, (M, Mgh,) and an announcing, to him; so the calling, or summoning, by reason to frequent usage of this word [as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making a sign with a garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"], came to be thus called; and one said of the caller, or summoner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vwab","text_ar":"ثوَب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) or it means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summoning, twice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repeating a call"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summons;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vAb","text_ar":"ثاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he returned: ” (Mgh:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vw~b","text_ar":"ثوّب"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above, (T, Msb,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he called,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"summoned, one time after another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he repeated his call,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tvwyb","text_ar":"تثويب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*aAn","text_ar":"اَذَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, Msb;) i. e., the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^a*~in","text_ar":"مُوَذِّن"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after having, by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*An","text_ar":"اذان"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called the people to prayer,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaAho raHimakumu A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"الصَّلَاهْ رَحِمَكُمُ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaAho","text_ar":"الصَّلَاهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prayer: may God have mercy on you! Prayer!"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; thus calling to it a second time: (T:) or his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the morning call to prayer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaApu xayorN mina Aln~awomN","text_ar":"الصَّلَاةُ خَيْرٌ مِنَ النَّوْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prayer is better than sleep"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, TA;) for he resumes his call by saying this after he has said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a EalaY","text_ar":"حَىَّ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaAho","text_ar":"الصَّلَاهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a EalaY AlfalaAHN","text_ar":"حَىَّ عَلَى الفَلَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; desiring the people to hasten to prayer: (TA:) or his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying, in the morning call to prayer,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlSlAp xyrmn Alnwm","text_ar":"الصلاة خيرمن النوم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"after having said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~ Ely AlSlAh","text_ar":"حَىّ علي الصلاه"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HY~ Ely AlflAH","text_ar":"حىّ علي الفلاح"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T:) or the old"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tvwyb","text_ar":"تثويب"},{"kind":"text","text":"was the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^a*~in","text_ar":"مُوَذِّن"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the morning call to prayer,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlSlAp xyr mn Alnwm","text_ar":"الصلاة خير من النوم"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the modern,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaAho AlS~alaAho","text_ar":"الصَّلَاهْ الصَّلَاهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAmato qaAmato","text_ar":"قَامَتْ قَامَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.) It also signifies The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iqaAmap","text_ar":"اـِقَامَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, K, TA;) [meaning, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chanting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubal~iguwn","text_ar":"مُبَلِّغُون"},{"kind":"text","text":", in a mosque, not by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^a*~in","text_ar":"مُوَذِّن"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the common words of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*aAn","text_ar":"اَذَان"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the addition of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado qaAmati AlS~alaAho","text_ar":"قَدْ قَامَتِ الصَّلَاهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time of prayer has come"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronounced twice after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HY~","text_ar":"حىّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY AlflAH","text_ar":"على الفلاح"},{"kind":"text","text":";] i. e. the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AqAmp","text_ar":"اقامة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of prayer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) and this is what is meant by the phrase, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA vuw~iba biAlS~alaApi","text_ar":"اـِذَا ثُوِّبَ بِالصَّلَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the words of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AqAmp","text_ar":"اقامة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are chanted"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAth, Mgh, TA.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"praying after the prayer divinely ordained."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yoo, T, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vw~b","text_ar":"ثوّب"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He performed a supererogatory prayer after the prescribed;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tvwyb","text_ar":"تثويب"},{"kind":"text","text":"being only after the prescribed; being the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"praying after praying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tvw~b","text_ar":"تثوّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v~wb birakoEatayoni","text_ar":"ثّوب بِرَكْعَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He performed two rek'ahs as a supererogatory act."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) But this and the similar significations are said to be post-classical. (MF.) ―         -b4-  See also 4, in four places.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vay~abato","text_ar":"ثَيَّبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, Mgh,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tavoyiybN","text_ar":"تَثْيِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, Mgh;) formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vay~ibN","text_ar":"ثَيِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", upon supposition [that the medial radical letter of this word is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":", whereas many hold that letter to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Mgh;) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tavay~abato","text_ar":"تَثَيَّبَتْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vyb","text_ar":"ثيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [the author of which seems to have supposed that, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vay~abato","text_ar":"ثَيَّبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", one should read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuy~ibato","text_ar":"ثُيِّبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and therefore he gives"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvay~abN","text_ar":"مُثَيَّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vay~ibN","text_ar":"ثَيِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became what"},{"kind":"page_break","n":362},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vay~ib","text_ar":"ثَيِّب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, Mgh, K.) ―         -b2-  [Accord. to my copy of the Mgh, it also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAb","text_ar":"نَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":": but I think that, in this instance, it is a mistranscription, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nay~abato","text_ar":"نَيَّبَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-  [See also the last sentence of the second paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vrb","text_ar":"ثرب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and compare, with what is there said by SM, meanings assigned below to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavaAbN","text_ar":"مَثَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavaAbapN","text_ar":"مَثَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["M","Mgh","K","T","Msb","S","TA","IAth"]},{"entry_id":"n4802","headword_ar":"ثَوْبٌ","root":"vwb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, Msb, K,) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stuff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is worn by men, composed of linen, cotton, wool, fur,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaz~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) but [properly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not what is cut out of several pieces, such as the shirt, and trousers, or drawers, &c.;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;) [though often applied to a shirt or shift ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamiyS","text_ar":"قَمِيص"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diroE","text_ar":"دِرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":") and to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jub~ap","text_ar":"جُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:] it seems to be so called because the wearer returns to it, or it to the wearer, time after time: (Mgh:) [also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment worn by women and girls over the shift;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSodapN","text_ar":"اُصْدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";) app., as in the present day,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long gown, reaching to the feet, with very wide sleeves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAbN","text_ar":"ثِيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the pl. of mult.] (T, S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avowaAbN","text_ar":"اَثْوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] (S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avowubN","text_ar":"اَثْوُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avow^ubN","text_ar":"اَثْوُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) the last two being pls. of pauc., and the latter of them being thus pronounced with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"by some of the Arabs because the dammeh immediately after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is deemed difficult of utterance; for which reason they substitute"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in all instances like this. (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Curtains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"are not [properly] called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAb","text_ar":"ثِيَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amotiEapu Albayoti","text_ar":"اَمْتِعَةُ البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) though Es-Sarakhsee uses the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAbu Albayoti","text_ar":"ثِيَابُ البَيْتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEal~aqa biviyaAbi","text_ar":"تَعَلَّقَ بِثِيَابِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clung to the curtains"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the House"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of God"},{"kind":"text","text":"], i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the curtains of the Kaabeh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a tropical expression. (A.) ―         -b3-  Sometimes,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobN","text_ar":"ثَوْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used metonymically to signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that veils, covers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protects:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying of a poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"kavawobi A@boni biyDK waqaAhumo bihi\n                      \n                     \n                        fasad~a EalaY Als~aAlikiyna Als~abiylaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like the means of protection adopted by Ibn-Beed: he protected them by it, and closed the way against the passengers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) Ibn-Beed was a wealthy merchant of the tribe of 'Ád, who hamstrung his she-camel upon a mountain-road, and stopped the way [to his abode] with it. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byD","text_ar":"بيض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  In the same manner, also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAbN","text_ar":"ثِيَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used to signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weapons."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 63.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avowaAbN","text_ar":"اَثْوَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes employed to signify (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wearers of garments;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the wearers'"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodies."},{"kind":"text","text":"(R, TA.) Esh-Shemmákh says, (T,) or Leylà, describing camels, (TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wamawohaA biA^avowaAbK xifaAfK falaA taraY\n                      \n                     \n                        lahaA  $abahFA A_il~aA Aln~aEaAma Almunaf~araA"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They mounted them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, the travellingcamels, (T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"text","text":"their ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agile,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and thou seest not anything like them, except ostriches scared away."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (T, TA.) And in like manner, also, the dual is employed to signify (assumed tropical:)  The wearer's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"self;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what the garments infold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAb","text_ar":"ثِيَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is employed in the same manner. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lil~hi vawobaAhu","text_ar":"لِلّهِ ثَوْبَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To God be he"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his excellence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attributed!"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for nothing but what is excellent is to be attributed to God:] (A:) or it means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lil~hi dar~uhu","text_ar":"لِلّهِ دَرُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To God be attributed the good that hath proceeded from him!"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his good deed!"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alh","text_ar":"اله"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dr","text_ar":"در"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY vawobaYo A^abiY A^ano A^afiyahu","text_ar":"فِى ثَوْبَىْ اَبِى اَنْ اَفِيَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"On me and on my father it rests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be it, that I pay it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY*im~atiY wa*im~apiA^abiY","text_ar":"فِىذِمَّتِى وَذِمَّةِاَبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on my responsibility and the responsibility of my father"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ausolulo viyaAbaka mino viyaAbiY","text_ar":"اُسْلُلْ ثِيَابَكَ مِنْ ثِيَابِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Withdraw,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separate, thyself from me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b6-  [The following exs. are mostly, or all, tropical.] ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~i Almay~ita","text_ar":"اـِنِّ المَيِّتَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layuboEavu fiY viyaAbihi Al~atiY yamuwtu fiyhaA","text_ar":"لَيُبْعَثُ فِى ثِيَابِهِ الَّتِى يَمُوتُ فِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, * TA,) a saying of Mohammad, repeated by Aboo-Sa'eed El-Khudree, when, being about to die, he had called for new garments, and put them on: (TA:) it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the dead will be raised in his garments in which he dies;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to some; and was used in this sense by Aboo-Sa'eed: (ElKhattábee, MF, TA:) or (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agreeably with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his works"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which his life is closed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the state in which he dies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"according as it is good or evil. (TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waviyaAbaka faTah~iro","text_ar":"وَثِيَابَكَ فَطَهِّرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [lxxiv. 4], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And purify thy garments:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Abbás, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shorten thy garments;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the shortening them is a means of purity: (T:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put not on thy garments in a state of disobedience or unrighteousness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I'Ab, T:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be not perfidious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for [figuratively speaking,] he who is so pollutes his garments: (Fr, T:) or, as some say, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purify thy heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l-'Abbás, T, K:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purify thyself"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKt, T, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from sins,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offences:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKt, TA:) or (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rectify thine actions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy conduct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAno naqiY~u Alv~awobi","text_ar":"فُلَانْ نَقِىُّ الثَّوْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is free from vice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fault:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAhiru Alv~awobi","text_ar":"طَاهِرُ الثَّوْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure in heart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reputation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nSH","text_ar":"نصح"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"danisu Alv~iyaAbi","text_ar":"دَنِسُ الثِّيَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Vicious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faulty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfidious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil, in reputation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"actions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the way that he follows"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with respect to religion and morality"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAbisi vawobaYo zuwrK","text_ar":"كَلَابِسِ ثَوْبَىْ زُورٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muta$ab~iEN","text_ar":"مُتَشَبِّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoraDa vawobu","text_ar":"اَعْرَضَ ثَوْبُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almalobasi","text_ar":"المَلْبَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almilobasi","text_ar":"المِلْبَسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaruDa","text_ar":"عَرُضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"ثَوْبُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The membrane called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alaY","text_ar":"السَّلَى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Algirosu","text_ar":"الغِرْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K. See these two words.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Mgh","Msb","K","T","S","A","TA","Fr","IKt"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}